With Russia constantly in the news, here is a photograph from a story named ‚ÄúThe Putin Generation‚Äù in the December issue of National Geographic Magazine. It examined the attitudes and outlooks of young people in Russia, now in their mid-twenties, who were barely ten years old when Putin first became President.

Supporters of the Other Russia, an extremist opposition party, rally in Moscow, displaying flags and armbands with their symbol, a hand grenade. The Other Russia was formed by members of the banned ultranationalist National Bolshevik Party, originally founded by poet Eduard Limonov, but it is not recognized by Putin‚Äôs government.

