Only the spire of medieval St. Michael‚Äôs church remains on Glastonbury Tor, a hill visible from afar in Somerset County, England. According to the Arthurian legend, it is the entrance to Avalon ‚Äì a mythical place where the fabled king awaits his return into this world. The Tor has been identified with King Arthur since the alleged discovery of King Arthur and Queen Guinevere‚Äôs coffins in Glastonbury Abbey in 1191. 
This photograph is included in my new book ‚Äúminus 2/3‚Äù. In the book, I take the viewer behind the scenes of many of my images to share my approach to lighting with small flash. Signed copies of the book are available in my website.

